Hey [Customer Name],

Thank you for the quick reply.

I am working with carid.com, here's an example webpage: https://www.carid.com/2023-toyota-rav4-taillights/replacement-factory-replacement-tail-lights-fiber-optic-led-6148879460.html

On that page in the dataLayer on the first object there is a key/value pair; productCategory: "tail lights".

So if let's say I want to show the box if "tail lights" is true in the productCategory in the dataLayer would I do a custom javascript function condition like the following?

function digohCustomBoxCondition() {
    if (Array.isArray(window.dataLayer) && window.dataLayer.length > 0) {
        return window.dataLayer[0].productCategory === "tail lights";
    }
    return false;
}

Thank you,
